"about 1334":"about 1334","1295":"1295","about 1295":"about 1295","Salzwedel, Altmarkkreis Salzwedel, Saxony-Anhalt, Germany":"Salzwedel, Altmarkkreis Salzwedel, Saxony-Anhalt, Germany","Denmark":"Denmark","Germany":"Germany","nameMeanings":[{"name":"von","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Altered form of Welsh   Vaughan  .","Chinese: variant of   Wong  .","Cambodian: written វ៉ុន, unexplained."],"variants":[{"name":"Vaughan","meanings":["Welsh: from <i>fychan</i>, a lenited form of <i>bychan</i>, a diminutive of <i>bach</i> ‘little’. This was often used to distinguish the younger of two bearers of the same personal name, typically the son of a father with the same name."]}]},{"name":"Margarethe","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["from Greek.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margaret","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."]},{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretha","meanings":["from Greek.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Margarethe von Gützkow was born about 1259, in Salzwedel, Altmarkkreis Salzwedel, Saxony-Anhalt, Germany, her father, Jaczo II von Gützkow, was 17 and her mother, Cacislawa von Putbus, was 14. She had at least 2 sons with Laurids Saltensee. She died about 1334, in Denmark, at the age of 77."},"et":{"about 1259–about 1334":"umbes 1259–umbes 1334","1259–1334":"1259–1334","1228–Male":"1228–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1244–1303":"1244–1303","1247–1295":"1247–1295","1228":"1228","1303":"1303","1259":"1259","1247":"1247","1334":"1334","about 1259":"umbes 1259","about 1303":"umbes 1303","1244":"1244","about 1334":"umbes 1334","1295":"1295","about 1295":"umbes 1295","Salzwedel, Altmarkkreis Salzwedel, Saxony-Anhalt, Germany":"Salzwedel, Altmarkkreis Salzwedel, Sachsen-Anhalt, Saksamaa","Denmark":"Taani","Germany":"Saksamaa"},"fi":{"about 1259–about 1334":"noin 1259–noin 1334","1259–1334":"1259–1334","1228–Male":"1228–Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1244–1303":"1244–1303","1247–1295":"1247–1295","1228":"1228","1303":"1303","1259":"1259","1247":"1247","1334":"1334","about 1259":"noin 1259","about 1303":"noin 1303","1244":"1244","about 1334":"noin 1334","1295":"1295","about 1295":"noin 1295","Salzwedel, Altmarkkreis Salzwedel, Saxony-Anhalt, Germany":"Salzwedel, Altmarkkreis Salzwedel, Sachsen-Anhalt, Saksa","Denmark":"Tanska","Germany":"Saksa"},"fr":{"about 1259–about 1334":"environ 1259–environ 1334","1259–1334":"1259–1334","1228–Male":"1228–Décédé","–Male":"Décédé","1244–1303":"1244–1303","1247–1295":"1247–1295","1228":"1228","1303":"1303","1259":"1259","1247":"1247","1334":"1334","about 1259":"environ 1259","about 1303":"environ 1303","1244":"1244","about 1334":"environ 1334","1295":"1295","about 1295":"environ 1295","Salzwedel, Altmarkkreis Salzwedel, Saxony-Anhalt, Germany":"Salz